name: Nike Dunk High Wu-Tang (2024)

details.description:
The Nike Dunk High Wu-Tang (2024) brings back one of the most legendary sneaker collaborations in history. First released in 1999, the original Wu-Tang Dunk High was one of the earliest examples of a sneaker partnership with a music group, setting the stage for the future of sneaker culture. Finished in the Wu-Tang Clan's signature black and goldenrod color scheme, this 2024 retro release stays true to the original with its bold, eye-catching design. The custom Wu-Tang logo on the heel and tongue label remains an iconic detail, paying tribute to the group's legacy.

The Wu-Tang Dunk High features a premium leather upper in striking black and yellow, giving the sneaker a high-quality look and feel. Its classic high-top design offers support and comfort, making it perfect for both casual wear and street style. The sneaker’s retro roots, combined with the Wu-Tang Clan’s influence on music and culture, make this an essential addition for fans of both hip-hop and sneaker culture. Nike’s return of this historic design is sure to draw significant attention from collectors and enthusiasts alike.

Released on September 28, 2024, the Nike Dunk High Wu-Tang retailed for $150. This limited-edition sneaker is not just a piece of footwear—it’s a cultural artifact that celebrates the intersection of music and fashion, making it one of the year’s most highly anticipated releases.

name: Nike Dunk High Panda Black White (2021/2024)

details.description:
The Nike Dunk High Panda Black White 2021 features a smooth white leather upper with perforations on the toe box. Black leather overlays, eyestays and Swooshes match the black laces. The rubber outsole is black with a concentric-circles pattern for traction. The midsole is white with visible threading around the shoe. Black Nike branding appears on the white tongue and the heel features a black loop with arcs of white-on-white horizontal threading below it.
​
​ The Nike Dunk High Panda Black White 2021 was released on January 27, 2022 at a retail price of $115. The Nike Dunk High Panda also re-released in 2024.

name: Nike Dunk High PRM Vintage Pecan Sail

details.description:
A traditional two-toned aesthetic of pecan brown and white is featured on the Nike Dunk High PRM Certified Fresh Brown, with a university blue lacing that adds a flash color.

The sneaker features a white base that appears to be made of a canvas-like material. The Dunk High PRM by Nike also features a tumbled brown leather overlay. Finally, a sturdy rubber outsole with a sail-like color completes the appearance and lends it a somewhat retro vibe.

The Nike Dunk High PRM Certified Fresh Brown debuted on the market on September 9th, 2022, with a suggested retail price of $135.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Di'orr Greenwood Navajo Arts

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk High Di'orr Greenwood Navajo Arts is a skateboarding shoe inspired by iconic basketball shoe designs and Navajo culture.

This sneaker was designed by Di'Orr Greenwood, an artist and member of the Navajo Nation. It includes elements that pay tribute to Greenwood’s heritage. For example, the Big Dipper constellation, known as Nahookos Bika, is stitched across the Swoosh logo on the lateral side panels. Small white stars decorate the Swoosh on the medial side and the panels that form the lace cage. In addition, while some perforations across the vamp are regular holes, others are star-shaped cutouts. The upper comes in leather and features contrasting panels in Turquoise Blue, Rugged Orange, and Black.

Our experts at StockX like the ribbon running the length of the tongue and displaying a gradient of yellow and orange hues. The Nike SB Dunk High Di'orr Greenwood Navajo Arts was released on June 4, 2024, and sold for $145.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn boasts that recognizable Nike SB Dunk silhouette with a Halloween-inspired colorway and candy details.

A gradient of Amarillo and Orange covers the smooth leather upper and overlays before fading to white across the vamp. It appears almost spraypainted across the sneaker. This high-top skateboarding shoe features overlapping Swoosh logos in Orange and Amarillo on the left and right sides that connect around the heel. In addition, the Orange swoosh complements the laces and the stitching along the midsole. The rubber outsole provides traction and a burst of black that contrasts the bright colors on the upper.

Our experts at StockX love the Trick-or-Treat-inspired insole. It features graphics of candy corn with pennies, a nod to candy corn's status as the original "penny candy." The Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn was released on October 18, 2023, and retailed at $125.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Antihero Skateboards

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk High Antihero Skateboards is a high-top shoe designed as a partnership between the sportswear brand and the skateboard brand.

The Antihero Skateboards version of the Nike SB Dunk High has a leather upper. The base is an off-white, almost gray color which forms the sides, the perforated toe box, and even the eyestays and toe cap overlays. The Nike Swoosh appears in white leather on both sides, while the ankle strap that runs down to form the heel is also white leather. The tongue contains dual Antihero and Nike SB branding, while the heel contains a subtle embossed Antihero logo. The shoe sits on a white midsole and black outsole.

What we like best about this shoe is the textured leather upper, which adds visual interest even though the colors are neutral. The Nike SB Dunk High Antihero Skateboards was released on November 21, 2024, for $145.

name: Nike Dunk High Championship White Red

details.description:
Similar to classic Dunks from the mid-1980's, the Nike Dunk High Championship White Red carries a more traditional look with a two-tone color blocked leather upper. At the base, a matching Air sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk High Championship White Red released in May of 2022 and retailed for $115.

name: Nike Dunk High 1985 Red Acid Wash

details.description:
The Nike Dunk High 1985 Red Acid Wash features a dark grey leather upper with blotty Chile Red leather overlays and a monotone Swoosh. From there, a yellowed midsole and Nike woven tongue tag add a vintage touch.

The Nike Dunk High 1985 Red Acid Wash released in August of 2021 and retailed for $130.

name: Nike Dunk High Panda (2021) (Women's)

details.description:
The women's Nike Dunk High Panda (W) features white and black leather upper with a matching sole. From there, hits of red on the woven tongue label add some subtle flair.

The women's Nike Dunk High Black White (W) released in July of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Nike SB Dunk High FAUST Black Gold

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk High FAUST Black Gold, designed by New York-based graffiti artist FAUST, celebrates the 20th anniversary since the edition's launch.

The Dunk High FAUST has an all-black upper with regal pops of gold and metallic gold message embroidery tagged on the entire shoe. FAUST's motive was to tell different stories through the golden embroidery on these Nike Dunk High sneakers. The designer pairs this edition's premium leather with satin lining and soft underlays. For diversity in styling the laces, the shoe has four sets of laces.

The Nike SB Dunk High FAUST Black Gold were released in August 2022 with a retail price of $130.

name: Nike Dunk High Syracuse (2021)

details.description:
Nike continues to revive their famed Be True To Your School pack with the retro release of the Nike Dunk High Syracuse. The Nike Dunk High Syracuse first retroed in 2016 as a women’s exclusive, alongside other pack-mates, like the Villanovas, Kentuckys, and Michigans. Following the Syracuse-themed colorway releasing in Dunk Low form in 2020, the orange hue returns again in its original Dunk High form.

The Nike Dunk High Syracuse is constructed in familiar Dunk High color blocking. Hits of orange leather add a bright contrast to white leather panels. From there, a white tongue tag with orange Nike branding and a vibrant orange outsole completes the design, making it a true OG return.

The Nike Dunk High Syracuse released in March of 2021 for $120.

name: Nike Dunk High Bodega Legend Fauna Brown

details.description:
2020 is the year full of surprises, as Nike collaborates with Boston-based boutique, Bodega, on the Nike Dunk High. Unlike any other Dunk to drop in 2020, this special partnership delivers a heavily detailed sneaker, which, described by the shop, is based on "Classic Americana". The unexpected release merges two sports, basketball and baseball, into one while hitting on cultural moments in American style and history.

Constructed to look like a traditional baseball mitt, the Nike Dunk High Bodega Legend Fauna Brown’s upper features a mix of textures and hues, as both suede and pebbled leather make up the majority of the sneaker. In addition to materials, specific details such as iron-branded Bodega on the medial side, jeweled tortoiseshell Nike Swoosh on the lateral side, and rawhide lacing throughout the sneaker’s entirety elevate the sneaker’s status. A stash pocket is added inside the tongue, a head nod to a baseball mitt’s inner webbed pocket.

The Nike Dunk High Bodega Legend Fauna Brown released in December 2020 for $120.

name: Nike Dunk High Retro Chenille Swoosh Safety Orange

details.description:
The Nike Dunk High University Chenille Swoosh Safety Orange is a brightly colored version of this classic high-top model. The Nike Dunk High was first released in 1985 as a part of the "Be True to Your School" collection that was designed for the basketball court.

This Nike Dunk High model has a rubber gum sole that is situated right below the white midsole. The body of the shoe is made from a mixture of leather and fabric. The base of the shoe is black, and it has orange overlays. There are bright orange laces that lay on top of the black tongue, and it also incorporates a perforated toebox.

A feature our team of experts enjoy about the Nike Dunk High University Chenille Swoosh Safety Orange is the bright orange Nike ‘Swoosh’ symbol on the side. This model was first made available for purchase on September 22nd, 2022, with a retail price that started at $110.

name: Nike SB Dunk High RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee

details.description:
The Nike Dunk SB High Gundam Black Thunder Blue sneaker comes in a mixture of metallic gold and thunder blue hues.

This SB High Nike Dunk uses a metallic black and blue-grey base, which is supplemented by some detailing in a blaze of orange. The thunder blue upper of this shoe is complemented by mecha-like details at the collar and the toebox. This sneaker comes in different sizes and colors. A black sole and lacing system complete the design.

The Nike Dunk SB High Gundam Black Thunder Blue retailed for $110 when it was initially introduced in the market on October 9th, 2021.

name: Nike Dunk High Pink Prime (Women's)

details.description:
The women's Nike Dunk High Pink Prime (W) features a smooth white leather upper with Pink Prime overlays and Swooshes. From there, a woven Nike tongue label and matching sole complete the design.

The women's Nike Dunk High Pink Prime (W) releases in May of 2022 and retails for $115.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Run The Jewels

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk High Run The Jewels come in an active pink and black color palette.

The High Run Jewels The Nike SB Dunk's upper is crafted from a vibrant active pink suede material. The shoe features intricate details, including black overlays for contrast. The sneaker's cushioned midsole provides both cushioning and support. The shoe's outsole is created from a durable rubber material that provides grip and stability. The shoe features the trademark Nike Swoosh on the lateral sides and the signature Nike SB logo on the tongue.

The Nike SB Dunk High Run The Jewels were released on April 20, 2023, and was available for a retail price of $140.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Supreme Rammellzee

details.description:
Introducing the much-anticipated Nike SB Dunk High Supreme Rammellzee, released on August 31, 2023. This latest collab brings the legendary streetwear brand and art together, showcasing Rammellzee's iconic, vibrant artwork across the majority of the sneaker’s upper.

This bold sneaker fuses an abstract color palette throughout most of the sneaker fused with subtle white suede overlays on the mudguard and swoosh. Every angle of this shoe shouts Supreme's audacious style meshing with Rammellzee's legendary artistry. The heel counter, toe box, and mid panel all integrate eye-catching designs that align seamlessly with the overall aesthetic.

Launched on August 31, 2023, the Nike SB Dunk High x Supreme Rammellzee was an instant classic, retailing at $148.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Strawberry Cough

details.description:
Designed by Nike SB legend Todd Bratrud, the Nike SB Dunk High Strawberry Cough is composed of red ostrich-textual leather with shaggy green suede overlays and a green velour collar. From there, a graphic of a strawberry coughing embroidered on the heel and a semi-translucent sole add a custom feel.

The Nike SB Dunk High Strawberry Cough released in October of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Nike SB Dunk High Pro froSkate All Love

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk High Pro froSkate All Love comes in a white and Metallic Gold-University Red colorway. The upper part of this sneaker is made up of 100% leather material.

There is a branding of 'FroSkate' as well as 'All Love No Hate' on this shoe's graphic insoles, transparent outsoles, and on the tongue tags. Branding also appears on the white midsoles, the black Swooshes, and the quilted inner liners. The 'All Love, No Hate' slogan has been debossed in white leather on the upper, and a heart-shaped perforated toe box completes the look.

The Nike SB Dunk High Pro froSkate All Love debuted on November 30, 2022, with a retail price of $130.

name: Nike Dunk High 1985 SP Yellow Acid Wash

details.description:
The Nike Dunk High 1985 Yellow Acid Wash celebrates the aged effects of sneakers over time. Washed out black and yellow graphic overlays emphasize the appearance of wear and tear, while yellowed soles nod to the oxidation process. Also, these Dunks arrive in the design's original, high-cut form, explaining why they have a different shape from other Dunk Highs, which have more of a mid-cut silhouette.

The Nike Dunk High 1985 Yellow Acid Wash released in February of 2022 and retailed for $130.
